data.title: Can you name all 10 of these charlton characters?
data.text:
Quote:

Originally Posted by daywalker

Quote:

Originally Posted by DrWatson

I might know three. Is the guy below the Blue Beetle the Six Million Dollar Man?

Yes it is!

Add the Phantom and I'm done. Baron Weirwulf is the bottom left. I don’t remember the two characters’ names on the bottom right but they are the hosts of ghost manor and ghostly tales. The top three on the right I have no idea. Quote:

Originally Posted by michaelekrupp

Baron Weirwulf is the bottom left. I don’t remember the two characters’ names on the bottom right but they are the hosts of ghost manor and ghostly tales. The top three on the right I have no idea.

Now I don't feel so bad. The bottom right is Mr Bones or Mr Bone, something like that. I got Baron Weirwulf also, but those top right three are bugging me. Three, like most of you. I recognize two or three others from the horror comics (like @michaelekrupp said), but have no idea of their names. Quote:

Originally Posted by Jesse_O

Quote:

Originally Posted by michaelekrupp

Baron Weirwulf is the bottom left. I don’t remember the two characters’ names on the bottom right but they are the hosts of ghost manor and ghostly tales. The top three on the right I have no idea.

Now I don't feel so bad. The bottom right is Mr Bones or Mr Bone, something like that. I got Baron Weirwulf also, but those top right three are bugging me.

I can't even find them on search. just as an aside, I am watching The Monkeys and they just sang the Last Train to Clarksville. Also, Mike Nesmith had a guitar solo and he was fantastic, I've always known he was a real musician and went on to become a music producer. the whole Lee Majors thing reminded me of the greatness of classic TV.

P.S.

Still 3 Quote:

Nesmith also wrote Stone Poneys (Linda Ronstadt) Different Drum.

He's even more awesome than I gave him credit for, that's a great song. I even saw the monkey's play live!!! They were in reruns as a kid and they played in Toronto when i was like 10...so mid 80"s....it was great. A few years later i even got to see John Kay and Steppenwolf!!! I also had three ... Blue Beetle, Steve Austin, and The Phantom. I was really impressed that the artist captured Lee Majors well enough to recognize him. With such a small sketch? That's master-level caricature right there.
